commit.message:
Work around internal glib build failure in pkg-config

XCode 15.3 is treating some compile warnings as errors that it didn't before, breaking
the internal glib build in pkg-config.  Turn the errors back into warnings while the
pkg-config team addresses the underlying issue. (#4504)

Include configured title/album details in MPRIS plugin (#4493)

* Include configured title/album details in MPRIS plugin

If the main song list is configured to include the version in the title,
or the disc subtitle in the album, add these to the MPRIS metadata as
well, since MPRIS doesn't define any fields for them.

* Update quodlibet/ext/events/mpris/mpris2.py

---------

Co-authored-by: Nick Boultbee <declension@users.noreply.github.com>

* Include configured title/album details in MPRIS plugin

If the main song list is configured to include the version in the title,
or the disc subtitle in the album, add these to the MPRIS metadata as
well, since MPRIS doesn't define any fields for them.

* Update quodlibet/ext/events/mpris/mpris2.py

commit.message:
docs: update various fedora related broken links

Fixes #4496
CI: pin pytest in more places

Fix titlecase plugin not being loaded

Regression from #4358

Don't use the wrong spec to load the plugin, otherwise the first
loaded plugin will just be a namespace package and its content
will be ignored.

CI: stop limiting CI branches

it's just too annoying that I always have to adjust the CI config just to
run some tests, even on my fork
CI: update actions

wininst: pass --old-and-unmanageable to distutils

Somehow setuptools gets loaded now (we don't do it) and monkey patches
distutils in a broken way.

--old-and-unmanageable gives us the old behaviour back.

Fixes #4492
depchecker: api-ms-win-core-path also needs to be ignored

wininst: ignore ucrt libs in the dependency checker

those are system libs and don't need to be packaged, so it's fine
if they are missing.
tests: remove workaround for long unsupported flatpak runtime

gstreamer tests: skip silence-44-s.sv8.mpc always for now

I've filed an upstream bug for it:
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/gstreamer/-/issues/3369

Revert "Connect TreeViewHints->view leave-notify-event to __undisplay"

This reverts commit dc0dabc5888a9ff66fb7c2bfba5f65bc67c6e877.

This breaks the tooltips on Windows. In that they constantly hide and
show when moving the cursor.
Move to zlib 1.3.1.  The previous version is no longer available upstream. (#4491)
